article.headline: DePaul 83, Southern U. 46
article.story: ROSEMONT, Ill. -- Dar Tucker scored 21 points and Will Walker added 19 as DePaul beat Southern 83-46 in the second round of the Las Vegas Classic on Friday night. DePaul (6-4) used a barrage of first half 3-pointers -- including four from Tucker -- on the way to a 46-24 halftime lead. Tucker, a sophomore forward, hit 12-of-14 from the field. Mac Koshwal added 14 points and 10 rebounds. Southern (0-10) managed just 30 percent shooting and committed 20 turnovers. The Blue Demons cemented the win with a 12-0 run midway through the second half. The Jaguars' Chris Taylor, Tim Brown and Gregory Horne each led the team with eight points. The eight-team tournament resumes Monday at Las Vegas' Orleans Arena. Southern will play South Carolina-Upstate and DePaul will play Saint Louis.
